S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
EXTENDING DEEPEST CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF THE HONORABLE
RAYMOND H. BERETTA
Introduced By: Representatives Messier, Shekarchi, Blazejewski, Alzate, Stewart, Cruz,
Kennedy, Fogarty, Kislak, and Serpa
Date Introduced: January 21, 2025
Referred To: House read and passed
1 WHEREAS, It is with sadness that this House has learned of the passing of the
2 Honorable Raymond H. Beretta, the beloved husband of Joan for sixty-four years, and the proud
3 father of Raymond Jr., William, Amy, and Michael; and
4 WHEREAS, Born and raised in the City of Pawtucket, Mr. Beretta was a graduate of
5 Pawtucket West High School, and earned his Bachelor’s degree from Providence College and his
6 Master’s in Education from Rhode Island College; and
7 WHEREAS, For many years, Mr. Beretta was a school teacher with the Pawtucket
8 School Department until joining the family business, where he managed the Durastone/Flexicore
9 plant in Smithfield for twenty-one years. Ultimately, he returned to teaching, serving as the
10 Principal of Potter Burns Elementary until his retirement in 2000; and
11 WHEREAS, Dedicated to the community, in 1973, Mr. Beretta successfully ran for a seat
12 on the Pawtucket City Council. He had also been a member of the Knights of Columbus and the
13 Sons of Italy. He enjoyed spending leisure time golfing and boating, but the first and primary
14 love in his life was always his family, especially the time he spent with his grandchildren and
15 great grandchildren; and
16 WHEREAS, Raymond Beretta was a devoted family man, a great boss, a loyal friend,
17 and a consummate professional who had an innate ability to relate to people, staff, parents, and
18 especially students. He always approached life with a welcoming smile and a genuinely cheerful
19 nature, and he is deeply missed; now, therefore be it

1 RESOLVED, That this House of Representatives of the State of Rhode Island hereby
2 extends deepest sympathy and condolences on the passing of the Honorable Raymond H. Beretta;
3 and be it further
4 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and hereby is authorized and directed to
5 transmit a duly certified copy of this resolution to Mrs. Joan Beretta and Family.
